<br>
There is a gnomish watchman in north karana who asks you to kill 4 tiny skeletons and return their remains in a box.  He very very rarely appears.   <br>
<br>
I was level 25 when I attempted this, the tiny skeletons were all green to me and were very very hard to kill!  I'm a cleric, and even with my undead bane spells I had to meditate back up to kill another one.  2 attacking at once just about did me in.  Anyhow, it was trivial so I couldn't complete the quest.<br>
<br>
I do feel like this is possible to do, but only for a group of players that are low enough for the skeles.  it would be very tough.  I suppose asking to have this exempted would be justified by usefullness of the boots that are charged with SoW, something handy to have at any level.  Pair that with the rarity of the watchman showing up... I'd think that noone will ever complete this quest unless they wait for many rl hours or even days, with a group, for the watchman to appear<br>
<br>
I can do without these boots, as can many.  But I do feel it's a quest that people of all levels could benefit from.  if you want to add it to the list, feel free to do so.<br>
